    • Method Detail

      • doWithdraw

        public Boolean doWithdraw()
        Do withdraw cash, the core method in WithdrawController. The method will access all the instance variables through several private methods.
        Returns:
        true, if all the relevant hardwares work fine, the user does not cancel or get time out, and the process can get approval from the banking system over the network; otherwise return false.

      • doLoadAccounts

        private boolean doLoadAccounts()
        Do load accounts, a step of the overall process. It will change the current step, and access the accountNumbers. It will record the current step before return.
        Returns:
        true, if the accountNumbers gets a new value;

      • doGetAccountChoice

        private boolean doGetAccountChoice()
        Do get account choice, a step of the overall process. It will change the current step, and access the accountNumbers and accountNumber. It will record the current step before return.
        Returns:
        true, if the accountNumber is chosen by the user;

      • doGetWithdrawAmount

        private boolean doGetWithdrawAmount()
        Do get withdraw amount, a step of the overall process. It will change the current step, and access the withdrawAmount. It will record the current step before return.
        Returns:
        true, if the withdrawAmount gets a new value;

      • doCheckBalance

        private boolean doCheckBalance()
        Do check balance, a step of the overall process. It will change the current step, and access the balance. It will record the current step before return.
        Returns:
        true, if the balance is enough for withdraw;

      • doCheckInventory

        private boolean doCheckInventory()
        Do check inventory, a step of the overall process. It will change the current step, and access the cashInventory. It will record the current step before return.
        Returns:
        true, if the cashInventory is enough for withdraw;

      • doGetWithdrawPlan

        private boolean doGetWithdrawPlan()
        Do get withdraw plan, a step of the overall process. It will change the current step, and access the withdrawPlan. It will record the current step before return.
        Returns:
        true, if the withdrawPlan is valid for the cash dispenser;

      • doDispenseCash

        private boolean doDispenseCash()
        Do dispense cash, a step of the overall process. It will change the current step, and access the result. It will record the current step before return.
        Returns:
        true, if the cash is collected by the user before timeout;

      • doPrintAdvice

        private void doPrintAdvice()
        Do print advice, a step of the overall process. It will change the current step, and ask user for printing the advice. It will record the current step before return.
